1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 47-10 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to required disclosures before the sale of a condominium unit or a
3 property subject to a homeowners' association or a condominium project.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 47-10 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Required disclosures - Seller to provide .
8 1. As used in this section:
9 a. "Condominium" has the same meaning as provided under section 47 - 04.1 - 01 .
10 b. "Condominium project" means a real property development or plan consisting of
11 a condominium.
12 c. "Homeowners' association" means an organization making and enforcing rules
13 and guidelines for a residential subdivision or planned community.
14 2. By a mutually agreed upon date or within ten days of executing an agreement to sell
15 or transfer a property subject to the rules and regulations of a homeowners'
16 association or condominium project, the seller shall disclose in writing to a prospective
17 buyer:
18 a. A statement describing the amount of the periodic common expense assessment,
19 maintenance fees, or other charges and any unpaid common expenses or
20 special assessments currently due and payable from the seller;
21 b. The amount of approved special assessments;
22 c. A copy of the bylaws, amendments, supplemental declarations, rules, or
23 regulations of the homeowners' association or condominium project, official
